<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-912-805  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 912 805.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  Sept 11 1989 v11 n37 p37(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Networld grows up and takes its place among major shows.andO;(Connections) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Buerger, David.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Networld trade show has grown dramatically since it was firstheld in 1986.andP;  The first Networld, a Novell-sponsored Netware-onlyshow, drew only 2,450 people and 87 exhibitors.andP;  No longersponsored by Novell, Networld covers many different microcomputerlocal area network (LAN) systems.andP;  The 1989 show is expected todraw 20,000 people and 314 exhibitors.andP;  The desire of Networldattendees for technical tips and training is shown by the factthat 65 percent of all attendees preregister for all technicalseminars.andP;  Networld's success derives from the show's capacity forteaching and demonstrating network technology that works.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     NetWorldTrade ShowsLocal Area NetworksMicrocomputersSeminarsTechnical Instruction.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>